# Keep docs updated

When making changes that affect architecture, design decisions, or user-facing behaviour, update the relevant documentation:

- **docs/PRODUCT.md** — product requirements, design decisions, changelog
- **docs/ARCHITECTURE.md** — system pipeline, class hierarchy, build flow, server, frontend
- **docs/PARTS_ANATOMY.md** — physical design of each part, mechanical connections, materials, TODOs
- **docs/CSG_PATTERNS.md** — SolidPython2 idioms, custom primitives, modeling patterns
- **docs/VIEWER_ASSEMBLY.md** — stl_viewer.js behaviour, coordinate system, preview positions
- **docs/PARAMETERS.md** — parameter definitions, preview vs print orientation

When adding new `.cursor/rules/` files, mention them in the relevant docs so future agents know they exist.
